tlook-ai-trade-sp500-concerningly-expensive-rob-arnott-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esome%20of%20whom%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsteve-hanke-ai-boom-dotcom-bubble-tech-stocks-growth-forecasts-2025-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewe've%20covered%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20Business%20Insider).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20this%20week%2C%20equity%20strategists%20at%20Morgan%20Stanley%20and%20Goldman%20Sachs%20published%20new%20research%20outlining%20why%20AI%20stocks%20are%20%3Cem%3Enot%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20a%20bubble.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20of%20their%20main%20points%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bfcb84a4-d2c1-4184-a65d-cc3413f7ba5a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20you%20factor%20in%20earnings%20growth%2C%20cash%20flow%2C%20and%20profit%20margins%2C%20valuations%20don't%20look%20that%20high%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20overall%20point%20gets%20at%20the%20bull%20case%20referenced%20above%3A%20when%20you%20adjust%20valuations%20for%20alternate%20measures%20of%20corporate%20health%2C%20the%20picture%20is%20far%20less%20stark%2C%20and%20parallels%20to%20the%20dot-com%20era%20weaken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20the%20chart%20below%20from%20Morgan%20Stanley%2C%20for%20instance.%20It%20shows%20that%20the%20median%20free%20cash%20flow%20yield%20for%20the%20top%20500%20companies%20is%20roughly%20triple%20what%20it%20was%20in%201999.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22829%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22median%20stock%20cash%20flow%20yield%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e6a0b05dbc4fd10daa74be%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22466%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3ECompustat%2FMorgan%20Stanley%20Research%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20next%20chart%20%E2%80%94%20also%20from%20Morgan%20Stanley%20%E2%80%94%20shows%20the%20traditional%20forward%20price-to-earnings%20ratio%20with%20a%20twist%2C%20by%20adjusting%20for%20profit%20margins.%20The%20current%20level%20of%20this%20valuation%20metric%20is%20way%20lower%20than%20it%20was%20in%201999%2C%20because%20those%20margins%20are%20so%20much%20more%20robust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22866%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22S%26amp%3BP%20500%20forward%20normalized%20by%20profit%20margins%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e6a13f5dbc4fd10daa74cb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22551%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EFactSet%2FMorgan%20Stanley%20Research%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EGoldman%20offers%20yet%20another%20alternate%20valuation%20measure%2C%20this%20one%20designed%20to%20account%20for%20future%20earnings%20%3Cem%3Egrowth%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%20chart%20below%20shows%20the%20so-called%20PEG%20ratio%20over%20time%20for%20tech%20stocks%20(light%20blue%20line)%20and%20the%20MSCI%20all-world%20index%20(dark%20blue).%20Note%20that%20tech%20is%20far%20cheaper%20than%20it%20was%20in%201999%20%E2%80%94%20and%20far%20less%20decoupled%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22808%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22PEG%20ratio%2010-8%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68e6af0dcc993f9955cfd01d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22574%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EDatastream%2FGoldman%20Sachs%20Global%20Investment%20Research%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20one%20major%20reason%20alternative%20valuation%20metrics%20look%20attractive%20is%20because%20the%20biggest%20players%20in%20the%20dominant%20industry%20%E2%80%94%20AI%20%E2%80%94%20are%20stronger%20now%20than%20they%20were%20in%20the%20dot-com%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20looking%20at%20%26quot%3Bstrength%2C%26quot%3B%20Goldman%20is%20focused%20on%20a%20company's%20balance%20sheet.%20How%20much%20debt%20does%20it%20have%3F%20Does%20it%20have%20enough%20cash%20to%20pay%20that%20debt%20down%20and%20still%20reinvest%3F%20The%20firm%20says%20today's%20crop%20of%20e