%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-used-cars-are-still-so-expensive-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20used%20car%20sector%20%3C%2Fa%3Eis%20not%20back%20to%20normal.%20The%20average%20price%20of%20all%20used%20car%20transactions%20is%20below%20its%20pandemic%20peak%2C%20but%20still%20thousands%20of%20dollars%20more%20expensive%20than%20it%20was%20six%20years%20ago.%20Prices%20are%20creeping%20up%20again%2C%20too%3A%20The%20most%20recent%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20data%20shows%20they're%20up%206%25%20over%20the%20past%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20hangover%20effects%20from%20so%20much%20disruption%20from%20years%20ago%2C%20it's%20all%20playing%20out%20now%2C%26quot%3B%20Drury%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20tariffs%20in%20the%20mix%20and%20new%20car%20prices%20continuing%20to%20creep%20up%2C%20the%20future%20may%20be%20worse.%20The%20answer%20to%20the%20perennial%20question%20of%20when%20is%20the%20%26quot%3Bbest%20time%26quot%3B%20to%20buy%20a%20used%20car%20may%20now%20permanently%20be%20%26quot%3Bthere's%20no%20such%20thing%20as%20a%20best%20time.%26quot%3B%20And%20when%20it%20comes%20time%20to%20get%20a%20car%2C%20new%20or%20used%2C%20hope%20you%20have%20some%20time%20to%20shop%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOr%20as%20Drury%20puts%20it%3A%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20just%20reestablishing%20your%20expectations%2C%20but%20coming%20to%20terms%20with%20today's%20new%20reality%2C%20which%20is%20unfortunately%20not%20in%20your%20favor.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20state%20the%20obvious%2C%20before%20a%20car%20can%20be%20used%2C%20it%20has%20to%20be%20new.%20So%20when%20there's%20a%20slump%20in%20new%20cars%20rolling%20off%20the%20lot%2C%20that%20hits%20the%20used%20vehicle%20market%20down%20the%20road.%20According%20to%20data%20from%20Edmunds%2C%20millions%20fewer%20new%20cars%20have%20been%20sold%20in%20the%20US%20in%20recent%20years.%20Sixteen%20to%2017%20million%20new%20cars%20were%20sold%20annually%20in%20the%20US%20from%202014%20to%202019.%20From%202020%20to%202022%2C%20that%20number%20fell%20to%2013%20to%2014%20million%20each%20year.%20Sales%20have%20been%20creeping%20back%20up%20%E2%80%94%20Edmunds%20estimates%20sales%20will%20finally%20surpass%2016%20million%20again%20this%20year%20%E2%80%94%20but%20even%20with%20the%20rebound%2C%20the%20ripple%20effects%20of%20the%20pandemic-era%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchip-shortage-expected-cost-auto-industry-car-makers-110-billion-2021-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esemiconductor%20shortage%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20other%20supply-chain%20and%20sales%20headaches%20continue%20to%20have%20an%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThose%20vehicles%20never%20entered%20the%20vehicle%20ecosystem%20to%20become%20used%20vehicles%20for%20consumers%2C%20and%20that's%20the%20crux%20of%20the%20matter%20right%20now%2C%20it's%20that%20hole%20that%20was%20made%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Jeremy%20Robb%2C%20senior%20director%20of%20economic%20and%20industry%20insights%20at%20Cox%20Automotive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20simply%20aren't%20as%20many%20people%20going%20to%20dealerships%20looking%20to%20trade%20in%20cars%20they%20bought%20new%20two%2C%20three%2C%20or%20four%20years%20ago.%20And%20if%20they%20are%20turning%20up%2C%20it's%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Faffordable-used-cars-expensive-toyota-ford-honda-chevrolet-2022-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evehicles%20that%20were%20more%20expensive%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20first%20place%20because%20of%20pandemic-era%20pressures.%20Stephanie%20Brinley%2C%20an%20automotive%20analyst%20at%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%2C%20says%20that%20because%20of%20supply%20chain%20issues%2C%20carmakers%20focused%20on%20%26quot%3Btheir%20most%20popular%20models%20and%20their%20most%20popular%20trim%20levels%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20tended%20to%20be%20on%20the%20middle%20or%20high-end%20of%20their%20price%20range.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20you%20have%20a%20combination%20of%20a%20vehicle%20that%20was%20more%20expensive%20in%20the%20first%20place%20and%20relatively%20low%20supply%2C%26quot%3B%20Brinley%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F837Il%2Fembed.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22feedlyNoScript%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Line%20chart%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2F837Il%2Ffull.png%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fleasing-a-car-vs-buying-why-lease-is-a-good-idea-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ELeasing%20is%20a%20factor%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20too.%20Typically%2C%20about%2030%25%20new%20cars%20are%20leased%20every%20year%2C%20Robb%20explains%2C%20but%20that%20fell%20to%20about%2017%25%20in%202022.%20Automakers%20would%20rather%20customers%20simply%20buy%20a%20car%20outright%20%E2%80%94%20they%20make%20more%20off%20of%20it%20%E2%80%94%20so%20heightened%20consumer%20competition%20for%20a%20limited%20number%20of%20pricey%20new%20vehicles%20reduced%20the%20need%20for%20manufacturers%20to%20offer%20leasing%20terms%2C%20because%20they%20were%20selling%20premium%20cars%20for%20close%20to%20full%20price.%20Most%20leases%20mature%20in%2036%20months%2C%20at%20which%20point%20the%20car%20is%20often%20turned%20in%20and%20put%20on%20the%20used%20car%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20lease%20maturities%20have%20really%20been%20contracting%20over%20the%20past%20year%20and%20a%20half%20and%20will%20continue%20to%20contract%2C%26quot%3B%20Robb%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20the%20pandemic%2C%20there%20are%20other%20generally%20consumer-unfriendly%20shifts%20in%20the%20new%20car%20market%20that%20are%20trickling%20down%20to%20the%20used%20car%20market.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuying-car-vehicle-new-used-good-time-economic-uncertainty-tariffs-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20cars%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20gotten%20extremely%20expensive%20as%20people%20load%20up%20their%20vehicles%20with%20all%20sorts%20of%20pricey%20features%20and%20tech.%20Once%20a%20new%20car's%20price%20goes%20up%2C%20used%20cars%20of%20the%20same%20model%20go%20up%2C%20too%2C%20as%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20anchored%20together.%20American%20drivers%20lean%20toward%20bigger%2C%20pricier%20cars%2C%20which%20is%20fine%20with%20automakers%20since%20the%20larger%20models%20tend%20to%20produce%20more%20profits.%20Many%20more%20affordable%2C%20smaller%20vehicles%20have%20been%20pulled%20off%20the%20market%20altogether%20%E2%80%94%20RIP%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fford-focus-rs-first-drive-2016-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFord%20Focus%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Chevy%20Cruz%2C%20and%20Dodge%20Dart.%20The%20impact%20is%20multi-fold%3A%20Used%20cars%20are%20more%20expensive%20because%20they%20were%20more%20expensive%20when%20they%20were%20new%2C%20owners%20may%20be%20holding%20onto%20them%20longer%20to%20justify%20the%20higher%20price%20tag%2C%20and%20some%20more%20cost-conscious%20would-be%20new%20car%20buyers%20are%20being%20priced%20out%20of%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20seeing%20a%20great%20expansion%20of%20new%20vehicles%20and%20definitely%20not%20entry-level%20new%20vehicles%2C%20so%20the%20people%20who%20would%20look%20to%20a%20%2430%2C000%20entry-level%20model%20are%20forced%20into%20the%20used%20car%20market%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sam%20Fiorani%2C%20an%20industry%20analyst%20at%20AutoForecast%20Solutions.%20Some%20manufacturers%20are%20starting%20to%20notice%20the%20missing%20part%20of%20their%20lineups%20and%20fill%20it%2C%20but%20even%20those%20prices%20are%20going%20up%20quickly.%20%26quot%3BWhere%20entry-level%20was%20%2415%2C000%20not%20too%20long%20ago%2C%20it's%20suddenly%20closing%20in%20on%20%2430%2C000%2C%26quot%3B%20Fiorani%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEvery%20time%20you%20do%20something%20that%20raises%20the%20cost%20of%20a%20new%20car%2C%20they're%20at%20such%20high%20levels%20already%2C%20what%20you're%20really%20doing%20is%20creating%20another%20used%20vehicle%20consumer%2C%26quot%3B%20Robb%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20ask%20analysts%20and%20auto%20experts%20whether%20the%20used-car%20price%20picture%20is%20going%20to%20get%20brighter%20anytime%20soon%2C%20the%20answer%20is%20more%20or%20less%E2%80%A6%20not%20really.%20While%20vehicles%20are%20taking%20longer%20to%20sell%20as%20people%20hunt%20for%20deals%20and%20think%20it%20through%2C%20demand%20isn't%20coming%20down.%20Nathan%20Garnett%2C%20chief%20business%20officer%20at%20online%20marketplace%20OfferUp%2C%20tells%20me%20that%20even%20as%20listing%20prices%20for%20used%20cars%20have%20increased%20on%20the%20platform%20over%20the%20past%20year%2C%20sell-through%20rates%20have%20not%20budged.%20%26quot%3BBuyers%20are%20willing%20to%20pay%20those%20prices%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20sense%3A%20The%20US%20is%20very%20car-dependent%2C%20and%20if%20you%20need%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fall-ways-cars-suck-according-to-guy-who-wrote-book-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecar%20to%20get%20to%20work%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20school%20or%20the%20grocery%20store%2C%20you%20need%20a%20car%2C%20full%20stop.%20Plus%2C%20driving%20can%20be%20a%20fun%20and%20pleasant%20way%20to%20get%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20many%20other%20industries%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Ftrump-tariffs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ethe%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20an%20elephant%20in%20the%20room.%20Brinley%2C%20from%20S%26amp%3BP%20Global%2C%20says%20their%20implications%20are%20the%20%26quot%3Bthousand-dollar%20question.%26quot%3B%20Many%20automakers%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fautomakers-are-revealing-how-much-trumps-tariffs-are-costing-them-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eeating%20the%20costs%20of%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20that%20can't%20go%20on%20forever%20if%20trade%20uncertainty%20persists.%20Brinley%20says%20they're%20%26quot%3Bcautiously%20watching%26quot%3B%20for%20trade%20agreements%20with%20the%20EU%20and%20Japan%20to%20be%20solidified%2C%20but%20bigger%20questions%20loom%20around%20negotiations%20between%20the%20US%2C%20Canada%2C%20and%20Mexico%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20since%20the%20free%20trade%20deal%20between%20the%20three%20countries%20is%20up%20for%20review%20in%20July%202026.%20%26quot%3BIn%20the%20meantime%20of%20all%20of%20that%2C%20automakers%20are%20moving%20through%20a%20lot%2C%20so%20prices%20will%20come%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20tariffs%20haven't%20been%20a%20big%20factor%20so%20far%2C%20the%20anticipation%20of%20them%20caused%20some%20people%20to%20pull%20forward%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-consumers-buying-cars-retail-sales-price-increases-inventory-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Epurchase%20of%20a%20new%20car%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20avoid%20anticipated%20price%20hikes%20in%20the%20future.%20That's%20good%20for%20the%20used%20market%20in%20that%20they%20traded%20in%20their%20old%20car%2C%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20dealers%20who%20are%20also%20expecting%20higher%20prices%20paid%20more%20for%20trade-ins%20than%20they%20would%20have%20otherwise.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20messed%20with%20the%20market%20a%20bit%2C%26quot%3B%20Drury%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETariff-driven%20purchases%20haven't%20been%20linear%2C%20either%2C%20says%20Kevin%20Roberts%2C%20director%20of%20economic%20and%20market%20intelligence%20at%20CarGurus%2C%20a%20car%20research%20and%20sales%20website.%20They%20saw%20sales%20of%20new%20and%20used%20vehicles%20pick%20up%20in%20March%20and%20April%2C%20around%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-liberation-day-reciprocal-tariffs-speech-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELiberation%20Day%3C%2Fa%3E%20tariff%20announcements%2C%20normalize%2C%20and%20then%20pick%20back%20up%20again%20toward%20the%20end%20of%20the%20summer.%20%26quot%3BI%20think%20people%20were%20just%20kind%20of%20like%2C%20'Oh%2C%20prices%20could%20go%20up%20even%20further.%20I%20should%20go%20get%20a%20car%20now%20if%20I%20was%20kind%20of%20looking%20for%20one%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20more%20uncomfortable%20realities%20of%20the%20American%20economy%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20pandemic%20is%20that%20prices%20will%20not%20return%20to%20their%20previous%20levels.%20While%20inflation%20has%20slowed%2C%20we%20won't%20see%20widespread%20deflation%20(nor%20do%20we%20want%20to).%20That%20means%20resetting%20expectations%20before%20you%20walk%20onto%20the%20car%20lot%2C%20developing%20a%20bit%20of%20price%20tag%20amnesia%2C%20and%20kissing%20that%202013%20cost%20you%20may%20have%20in%20your%20head%20goodbye.%20There%20are%20surely%20deals%20to%20be%20had%2C%20but%20they're%20hard%20to%20find%2C%20and%20the%20%2420%2C000%20that%20might%20have%20gotten%20you%20a%20solid%203-year-old%20vehicle%2010%20years%20ago%20will%20now%20land%20you%20an%208-year-old%20car%20with%2080%2C000%20miles%20on%20it.%20On%20used%20vehicles%2C%20we've%20made%20our%20bed%2C%20and%20now%20we%20have%20to%20lie%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20make%20new%20used%20cars%2C%26quot%3B%20Fiorani%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Femily-stewart%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EEmily%20Stewart%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20senior%20correspondent%20at%20Business%20Insider%2C%20writing%20about%20business%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D